github.com/users/nivranaitsirhc/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2020-08-03T03:35:14Z","updated_at":"2020-08-03T03:35:14Z","body":"> \r\n> \r\n> It's not clear what warning you are talking about, but the idea is that folders should look identical on both sides, if they don't they are out of sync.\r\n> \r\n> Deleting files on one side and expecting them not to be deleted on the other is not really syncing, it's more like file transfer which is not a scenario syncthing is made for.\r\n\r\nThe warning is in the title \"Out of Sync\" on the receive only folders. Let say my android is the remote and has folder set to **Send Only** and my on my PC has a clone of that folder set **Receive Only**. My setup is to clone a folder from the remote but retains the files deleted on the remote by restoring using the \"Staggered File Versioning\".\r\n\r\nNow when a file is deleted on the remote but restored on the clone, It will appear as a \"Local Changes\" on the clone, but when a folder is deleted on the remote that contains file and restored on the clone, syncthing throws an \"Out of Sync\" warning.\r\n\r\n> \r\n> Also, how did you manage to open an issue with no labels?\r\n\r\nI was actually looking for that when I was opening this issue but github has been changing for me lately. ","author_association":"NONE","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/syncthing/syncthing/issues/comments/667785208/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"nivranaitsirhc","id":13590148,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEzNTkwMTQ4","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/13590148?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/nivranaitsirhc","html_url":"https://github.com/nivranaitsirhc","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nivranaitsirhc/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nivranaitsirhc/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nivranaitsirhc/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nivranaitsirhc/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nivranaitsirhc/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nivranaitsirhc/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nivranaitsirhc/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nivranaitsirhc/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nivranaitsirhc/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/syncthing/syncthing/issues/comments/667788845","html_url":"https://github.com/syncthing/syncthing/issues/6873#issuecomment-667788845","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/syncthing/syncthing/issues/6873","id":667788845,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY2Nzc4ODg0NQ==","user":{"login":"nivranaitsirhc","id":13590148,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEzNTkwMTQ4","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/13590148?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/nivranaitsirhc","html_url":"https://github.com/nivranaitsirhc","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nivranaitsirhc/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nivranaitsirhc/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nivranaitsirhc/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nivranaitsirhc/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nivranaitsirhc/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nivranaitsirhc/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nivranaitsirhc/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nivranaitsirhc/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nivranaitsirhc/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2020-08-03T03:52:24Z","updated_at":"2020-08-03T05:38:38Z","body":"> \r\n> \r\n> I think the issue is that receive only items aren't synced, thus the remote can delete the directory containing the receive only files without touching them. it seems reasonable to mark the deleted dir containing receive only items as receive only item too instead of gaining to sync/delete it.\r\n\r\nSo this why the \"Out of Sync\" is thrown out on the \"Receive Only\" folders.\r\n\r\nI would suggest a feature to be added to \"Receive Only\" folders, \"Read-Only/Add-Only\" sub-option to \"Receive Only\" Folders as this way folder/files can be modified if it exist but can never be deleted if it does not exist on the remote. Is this feasible or I am asking too much. ","author_association":"NONE","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/syncthing/syncthing/issues/comments/667788845/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"nivranaitsirhc","id":13590148,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEzNTkwMTQ4","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/13590148?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/nivranaitsirhc","html_url":"https://github.com/nivranaitsirhc","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nivranaitsirhc/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nivranaitsirhc/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nivranaitsirhc/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nivranaitsirhc/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nivranaitsirhc/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nivranaitsirhc/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nivranaitsirhc/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nivranaitsirhc/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nivranaitsirhc/received_events","type":"User","user_view_ty